verses.text_plain: Whither is thy beloved gone, O thou fairest among women? whither is thy beloved turned aside? that we may seek him with thee.
verses.verse_html: 1Whither is thy beloved gone, O thou fairest among women? whither is thy beloved turned aside? that we may seek him with thee.

verses.text_plain: My beloved is gone down into his garden, to the beds of spices, to feed in the gardens, and to gather lilies.
verses.verse_html: 2My beloved is gone down into his garden, to the beds of spices, to feed in the gardens, and to gather lilies.

verses.text_plain: I am my beloved’s, and my beloved is mine: he feedeth among the lilies.
verses.verse_html: 3I am my beloved’s, and my beloved is mine: he feedeth among the lilies.

verses.text_plain: Thou art beautiful, O my love, as Tirzah, comely as Jerusalem, terrible as an army with banners.
verses.verse_html: 4Thou art beautiful, O my love, as Tirzah, comely as Jerusalem, terrible as an army with banners.

verses.text_plain: Turn away thine eyes from me, for they have overcome me: thy hair is as a flock of goats that appear from Gilead.
verses.verse_html:
5Turn away thine eyes from me, for they have overcome me: thy hair is as a flock of goats that appear from Gilead. ▼
▼ overcome…: or, puffed me up

footnotes.body_html: ▼ overcome…: or, puffed me up

verses.text_plain: Thy teeth are as a flock of sheep which go up from the washing, whereof every one beareth twins, and there is not one barren among them.
verses.verse_html: 6Thy teeth are as a flock of sheep which go up from the washing, whereof every one beareth twins, and there is not one barren among them.

verses.text_plain: As a piece of a pomegranate are thy temples within thy locks.
verses.verse_html: 7As a piece of a pomegranate are thy temples within thy locks.

verses.text_plain: There are threescore queens, and fourscore concubines, and virgins without number.
verses.verse_html: 8There are threescore queens, and fourscore concubines, and virgins without number.

verses.text_plain: My dove, my undefiled is but one; she is the only one of her mother, she is the choice one of her that bare her. The daughters saw her, and blessed her; yea, the queens and the concubines, and they praised her.
verses.verse_html: 9My dove, my undefiled is but one; she is the only one of her mother, she is the choice one of her that bare her. The daughters saw her, and blessed her; yea, the queens and the concubines, and they praised her.

verses.text_plain: Who is she that looketh forth as the morning, fair as the moon, clear as the sun, and terrible as an army with banners?
verses.verse_html: 10Who is she that looketh forth as the morning, fair as the moon, clear as the sun, and terrible as an army with banners?

verses.text_plain: I went down into the garden of nuts to see the fruits of the valley, and to see whether the vine flourished, and the pomegranates budded.
verses.verse_html: 11I went down into the garden of nuts to see the fruits of the valley, and to see whether the vine flourished, and the pomegranates budded.

verses.text_plain: Or ever I was aware, my soul made me like the chariots of Amminadib.
verses.verse_html:
12Or ever I was aware, my soul made me like the chariots of Amminadib. ▼
▼ Or ever…: Heb. I knew not
 , ▼
▼ made…: or, set me on the chariots of my willing people

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Or ever…: Heb. I knew not
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Or ever…: Heb. I knew not

footnotes.body_text: ▼ made…: or, set me on the chariots of my willing people
footnotes.body_html: ▼ made…: or, set me on the chariots of my willing people

verses.text_plain: Return, return, O Shulamite; return, return, that we may look upon thee. What will ye see in the Shulamite? As it were the company of two armies.
verses.verse_html:
13Return, return, O Shulamite; return, return, that we may look upon thee. What will ye see in the Shulamite? As it were the company of two armies. ▼
▼ of…: or, of Mahanaim

tokens.text: upon thee. What will ye see

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: or, of Mahanaim
